&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Medical Science Liaison (MSL) / Regional Medical Lead (RML) serves as a field-based scientific leader responsible for advancing the medical strategy within a defined region. This role combines traditional MSL responsibilities with regional leadership oversight, strategic execution, and cross-functional collaboration to support cardiovascular assets across approved products and pipeline programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The individual acts as a scientific expert in cardiovascular disease (e.g., heart failure, cardiomyopathies, hypertension, cardiometabolic disease, etc.), builds trusted partnerships with key opinion leaders (KOLs), and drives regional medical excellence aligned with global and U.S. medical strategy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
